Calls by a bird in flight. Elevation: 310 m. Date added to IBC: December 3, 2017.

This bird was presumably on territory, due to the time of year. A fairly large nest was seen, but the bird itself was not. The vegetation was thick, as it was mid-summer, so it was difficult to get a look above, which is presumably where the bird was calling from. The calls were most likely as the result of entering the bird's territory. The habitat is a mixed woods consisting of hemlocks and other conifers in with various hardwoods. Adjacent to the woods is a bog/marsh area.
